        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Fix Codex monthly credit limit display",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- parse and propagate Codex monthly credit limits from Codex CLI, OAuth, and OpenAI dashboard payloads\n- prefer the monthly limit in menu, CLI, projection, and widget-facing credit displays\n- in auto mode, preserve valid OAuth usage and import only a CLI monthly limit when both sources expose the same verified account email\n- retain credits-only CLI account identity for safe reconciliation without changing the existing usage-only contract\n\n## Root Cause\n\nCodex auto mode could stop at a successful OAuth response containing `remaining = 0` but no monthly-limit field. The Codex CLI could provide the enterprise monthly limit, but the value never reached credit displays.\n\n## Safety\n\nThe fallback does not replace OAuth rate windows or identity. It rejects CLI enrichment when the CLI account is unknown or differs from the OAuth account, and preserves cancellation behavior and the original OAuth partial result on ordinary CLI failure.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter 'CodexOAuthCreditLimitTests|CodexBaselineCharacterizationTests|CodexUsageFetcherFallbackTests'` (32 tests, 3 suites)\n- broader affected-surface selection (287 tests, 18 suites)\n- `make check`\n- `make test` (513 selections, 43 groups)\n- full branch autoreview against current `main`: clean, no actionable findings (0.82 confidence)\n\n## Behavior proof\n\nThe contributor's redacted live check confirmed that the Codex CLI exposes `credits.codexCreditLimit` for the affected account when OAuth credits remaining is zero. The maintainer accepted that textual live proof level for landing; final cross-source reconciliation is covered deterministically by matching-account, mismatched-account, missing-identity, unavailable-CLI, and missing-limit tests. No additional real-account probe was run during maintainer repair.\n",
